South Korea to Crack Down on Illegal Activities at Gas Stations

-- B y   S h i n h y e   K a n g
-- 
2011-06-27T02:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-27/south-korea-to-crack-down-on-illegal-activities-at-gas-stations.html
South Korea  plans to curb illegal
activities at gas stations, such as stockpiling and refusing to
sell fuel, as refiners plan to end price cuts on July 6, the
Ministry of Knowledge Economy said in an e-mailed statement
today. South Korean refiners reduced the cost of gasoline and
diesel by 100 won a liter for three months on April 7.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shinhye Kang in Seoul at 
 skang24@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amit Prakash at 
 aprakash1@bloomberg.net . 